### Start Up Commands
#The following steps are all completed within packet tracer

###1. Select the router and navigate to the CLI tab to access the console
- No initial configuration dialog
- Return!

###2. To enter privileged exec mode use the command enable or en.
- enable 
# en

###3. Enter the global configuration mode
- configure terminal 
# config t

###4. Change the hostname of the router to R1
- hostname R1

###5. Override command with “do” and check what interfaces are available on the router
- do show ip interface brief
# do sh ip int brief

###6. Configure an interface / assign an ip address
- Interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
- ip address {IP address} {net mask}
- no shutdown
- end

###7. View entire configuration starting from hostname
- show run | begin hostname
# sh run | begin hostname

###8. Copy the running configuration to the startup configuration
- Copy run start

###9. Backup the current running configuration to flash memory
- Copy run flash:

###10. Back up the current running configuration to an ftp server if possible
- Copy run ftp
- {ftp IP address}
- {destination filename}

###11. Reload device and ensure the correct configuration runs
- reload

